INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  'faecb087-f0f2-4b34-9541-6bc49320f92e',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$styled_components Design Tokens — Eliminate Magic Numbers with a Theme$escape$,
  $escape$Hardcoding `#1a1a2e` or `padding: 12px` directly in styled-components is a maintenance trap. The fix is a typed theme object passed through `ThemeProvider` — every color, spacing step, and type scale becomes a named token consumed via the `theme` prop in interpolations.

Define your tokens in a single `theme.ts` file. Use a spacing scale (4-based or 8-based) so `theme.space[2]` always means 8px — no guessing. Typography tokens (`theme.fontSize.sm`, `theme.fontWeight.bold`) keep your type ramp consistent. For colors, group by intent: `theme.color.surface`, `theme.color.textPrimary`, `theme.color.brand` — not by hue.

Extend `DefaultTheme` via module augmentation so TypeScript enforces token names at every interpolation site. Mistype `theme.collor.brand` and the build fails — not the browser.

This approach makes global redesigns a one-file change: update the theme object, every component re-renders with the new values. No grep-and-replace across 200 component files.$escape$,
  $escape$// theme.ts
import 'styled-components';

export const theme = {
  color: { brand: '#6c63ff', surface: '#ffffff', textPrimary: '#1a1a2e' },
  space: [0, 4, 8, 16, 24, 32, 48, 64],
  fontSize: { sm: '0.875rem', md: '1rem', lg: '1.25rem' },
} as const;

export type AppTheme = typeof theme;

declare module 'styled-components' {
  export interface DefaultTheme extends AppTheme {}
}

// Button.ts
import styled from 'styled-components';

export const Button = styled.button`
  background: ${({ theme }) => theme.color.brand};
  padding: ${({ theme }) => theme.space[2]}px ${({ theme }) => theme.space[4]}px;
  font-size: ${({ theme }) => theme.fontSize.md};
`;$escape$,
