INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  '9d7adf19-be59-4699-a135-c005c12fc70e',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$styled-components — Mobile-First Breakpoints, Container Queries, and Fluid Typography$escape$,
  $escape$Define your breakpoint map once and consume it via a typed helper — this keeps `css` interpolations consistent across every component. Use `${media.md`}` inside a tagged template to layer styles mobile-first, so the base rule targets small screens and each breakpoint overrides upward.

For layout-aware styling, styled-components works cleanly with the CSS `@container` rule. Wrap your component's host element with `container-type: inline-size`, then use `@container (min-width: 400px)` inside the styled template. Unlike media queries, this reacts to the component's own available width — invaluable for design-system cards or sidebar widgets that render in variable contexts.

For fluid typography, interpolate a `clamp()` expression directly into the `font-size` property. No JS math, no resize listeners — the browser handles the interpolation between your min and max sizes across the defined viewport range. Pair this with `rem` units so users' browser font preferences are respected. Centralise the clamp formula in a utility so every heading component pulls from the same scale.$escape$,
  $escape$const breakpoints = { sm: '480px', md: '768px', lg: '1200px' };
const media = Object.fromEntries(
  Object.entries(breakpoints).map(([k, v]) => [
    k, (...args: Parameters<typeof css>) => css`@media (min-width: ${v}) { ${css(...args)} }`
  ])
) as Record<keyof typeof breakpoints, (...args: Parameters<typeof css>) => ReturnType<typeof css>>;

const Card = styled.article`
  container-type: inline-size;
  font-size: clamp(0.875rem, 1.5vw + 0.5rem, 1.125rem);
  padding: 1rem;

  ${media.md`padding: 2rem;`}

  @container (min-width: 400px) {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: auto 1fr;
  }
`;$escape$,
