INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  '82bb421f-cf4c-4bf6-9f0c-88ac4b497daa',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$styled_components — Wiring Design Tokens into Your Component Library with ThemeProvider$escape$,
  $escape$styled_components' ThemeProvider is the canonical bridge between your raw design tokens and every component in your library. Wrap your app once with ThemeProvider, pass a typed theme object, and every styled component downstream receives it via the props.theme injection — no prop drilling, no imports per-component.

Extend DefaultTheme in a declaration file to get full TypeScript inference on theme values inside tagged template literals. This means autocomplete on colors.primary.500 or spacing[4] directly inside your css helper calls.

For a scalable system, structure tokens as nested objects matching your design tool's layer (primitives → semantics → components). Semantic aliases like theme.colors.action.default pointing to a primitive prevent components from reaching into raw values. Use the css helper to build reusable mixins — focusRing, elevationShadow — that reference theme tokens and compose cleanly into any styled component. The attrs() method complements this by injecting theme-driven defaults (e.g., ARIA attributes) without exposing them as external props. This layering keeps your styling logic encapsulated, type-safe, and token-driven from end to end.$escape$,
  $escape$// theme.d.ts — extend DefaultTheme for full inference
import 'styled-components';
declare module 'styled-components' {
  export interface DefaultTheme {
    colors: { action: { default: string; hover: string } };
    radii: { md: string };
  }
}

// Button.tsx
import styled, { css } from 'styled-components';

const focusRing = css`
  outline: 2px solid ${({ theme }) => theme.colors.action.default};
  outline-offset: 2px;
`;

export const Button = styled.button`
  background: ${({ theme }) => theme.colors.action.default};
  border-radius: ${({ theme }) => theme.radii.md};
  &:focus-visible { ${focusRing} }
  &:hover { background: ${({ theme }) => theme.colors.action.hover}; }
`;$escape$,
  $escape$typescript$escape$,
